About Us Payment Shipping Returns Contact Us
 
About us

Part of Ringwood for almost thirty years, we are now even more committed to providing our customers a great experience on the road and off it. Here at Le Tour Cycles, we do things a little bit differently. Many companies pay lip-service to things like customer service and value-for-money. We deliver. Our customers come back again and again because they know that they will get what they want, when they want it, with all the help they need. Come in, have a chat and get riding!

Unlike some companies that treat their online customers as an afterthought, we value all our customers. We have invested in online systems designed to make your online shopping experience as pleasant, secure and efficient as possible. We back up these systems with a reliable and cost-effective delivery system to ensure you get your order quickly. If you do run into any problems, we are always just a phone call or an email away.

We sell only quality brands from authorised local distributors with full Australian warranty support.

Please Note: Online pricing and stock range availability may be different in store
Payment

Le Tour Cycles accept payment via:

- Paypal
- Credit Cards (MasterCard, VISA)
- Bank deposit
- Pay via phone with credit/debit card on 1800 LETOUR
- Pay on pick up is fine but orders need to be organised in advance please call 1800 LETOUR to process an order.

We do not charge a surcharge for any payment method.

After you purchase any item, payment information will be automatically sent to you.

Please ensure you include your FULL NAME in the description field so we can trace the payment to your purchase.

We will have no way of tracing your payment and delays will result.

Our bank is:

Bank: Bendigo Bank
Account Name: Giro Australia Pty Ltd.
BSB: 633000
ACC: 146635370
Shipping

Orders ship via Australia Post or Courier within 24 hours of us receiving payment (excluding weekends). Please be aware that delivery times are dependent on your location and distance from our distribution centre in Melbourne.

For delivery within Australia please allow an estimated 2 - 7 Business Days from the day we receive payment for your order to arrive. For International delivery please allow an estimated 7 - 28 Business Days from the day we receive payment for your order to arrive.

INTERNATIONAL BUYERS please note that Import duties, taxes, and charges are not included in the item price or shipping cost. These charges are the buyer's responsibility.Please check with your country's customs office to determine what these additional costs will be prior to purchasing. All international parcels are sent via Express Registered Courier.

All items are securely packed in protective mailers or cartons. We do not ship to some international locations, see Postage & Payments tab for excluded countries.
Returns

All products purchased from Le Tour Cycles come with the full Australian manufacturer's warranty. If you should have any issue please message us via eBay and we will be more than happy to help.

All returned products will be tested and inspected for defects. If the item is faulty, we will post a working replacement.

If a replacement is unavailable, we will fully reimburse the customer. If the item is not faulty, it will be sent back at the customer's expense and no reimbursement will be offered.

Le Tour Cycles records the condition of items before they are sent out. Items that are claimed to be faulty and, when returned, exhibit damage incurred while in the customer's possession, will simply be sent back.

If the item is the incorrect size or does not suit your needs then you can return the item to us at the buyers expense. Please note that if it is in need of exchange there is a $10 resend fee for postage

These Terms and Conditions are in addition to, and do not replace or take away, your rights under Australian law: http://www.consumersonline.gov.au/Content/consumerrights/Refunds.asp

KAZAM KIDS BALANCE BIKE PINK
 
Swipe Left / Right to see more images
  
  
Item Description
Item Description
Skip the training wheels and teach kids to balance first using the award-winning KaZAM balance bike! KaZAM is the only run bike on the market uniquely designed with a foot rest. Children lift their feet up naturally and position them on to the foot rest maintaining proper balance and center of gravity similar to riding a traditional bicycle. It is the most realistic approach to learning coordination and balance; and ultimately teaching kids how to ride a pedaled bike.

KaZAM provides an alternative way to learn to ride a peddled bicycle based on the concept of balance first, pedal last. It is a training bicycle that assists children ages 3-6 to balance, increase coordination and ultimately ride a traditional bicycle for the first time with confidence. This customized kids bicycle has the steering and balancing challenges of a traditional bicycle but it has no pedals, chain or training wheels. It is uniquely designed with a foot rest area for balancing, thereby making the transition onto a peddled bicycle quicker and seamless!

Featuring:
• Design that teaches children to balance and increase coordination
• Step-through design features super-low stand over height and foot rest area
• Seat QR and pnuematic rubber 12" tyres
• Steel frame and spokes
• Adjustable chrome handlebars
• Soft padded grips
• Raised molded seat
• Quick-release seat adjustment
• Friction-free metal headset with bearings
• Air-inflated tyres
• East step in; patented footrest design
• Quality bike-dependent components
• Recommended for children aged 3-6 years old.
